////Rotator cuff - Complete (transmural) lesions (Snyder C)

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 - AC-Joint & Rotator Cuff of Shoulder MRI
And I select the radio button 'Finding'

When I select 'Rotator cuff' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Complete (transmural) lesions (Snyder C)' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial lesions' radio button is enabled

And 'Serial number' input field is enabled
And 'Image number' input field is enabled
And 'Import reference image' image uploader field is enabled

When I select 'Complete (transmural) lesions (Snyder C)' radio button
Then a non-interactive info image is visible
And 'Segment 1: Anterior (SSC)' radio button is enabled
And 'Segment 2: Antero-superior (rupture of coracohumeral ligament CHL)' radio button is enabled
And 'Segment 3: Superior (SSP)' radio button is enabled
And 'Segment 4: Postero-superior (SSP-ISP partial)' radio button is enabled
And 'Segment 5: Posterior (SSP-ISP)' radio button is enabled
And 'Segment 6: Total (SCC-SSP-ISP)' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Segment 1: Anterior (SSC)' radio button
Then 'Tendon retraction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Atrophy' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Tendon retraction' checkbox
And 'According to Bayne & Bateman' checkbox
Then 'Grade I: < 1 cm' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade II: 1 – 3 cm' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade III: 3 – 5 cm' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade IV: > 5 cm' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Atrophy' checkbox
And 'According to Goutallier' checkbox
Then 'Grade I: some fatty streaks' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade II: less than 50% fatty muscle atrophy' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade III: 50 % fatty muscle atrophy' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade IV: greater than 50% muscle atrophy' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Segment 2: Antero-superior (rupture of coracohumeral ligament CHL)' radio button
Then 'Tendon retraction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Atrophy' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Tendon retraction' checkbox
And 'According to Bayne & Bateman' checkbox
Then 'Grade I: < 1 cm' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade II: 1 – 3 cm' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade III: 3 – 5 cm' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade IV: > 5 cm' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Atrophy' checkbox
And 'According to Goutallier' checkbox
Then 'Grade I: some fatty streaks' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade II: less than 50% fatty muscle atrophy' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade III: 50 % fatty muscle atrophy' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade IV: greater than 50% muscle atrophy' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Segment 3: Superior (SSP)' radio button
Then 'Tendon retraction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Atrophy' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Tendon retraction' checkbox
Then 'According to Bayne & Bateman' radio button is enabled
And 'According to Patte' radio button is enabled

When I select 'According to Bayne & Bateman' radio button
Then 'Grade I: < 1 cm' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade II: 1 – 3 cm' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade III: 3 – 5 cm' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade IV: > 5 cm' radio button is enabled

When I select 'According to Patte' radio button
Then 'Stage I: Proximal tendon stump between tuberculum majus and apex' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage II: Proximal tendon stump between apex and glenoid margin' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage III: Proximal tendon stump at or behind glenoid level' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Atrophy' checkbox
Then 'According to Goutallier' radio button is enabled
And 'According to Zanetti' radio button is enabled

When I select 'According to Goutallier' radio button
Then 'Grade I: some fatty streaks' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade II: less than 50% fatty muscle atrophy' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade III: 50 % fatty muscle atrophy' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade IV: greater than 50% muscle atrophy' radio button is enabled

When I select 'According to Zanetti' radio button
Then 'Positive: SSP belly lies below line between upper surface of scapula and coracoid' radio button is enabled
And 'Negative' radio button is enabled

